Φ(MetabolicCost) = δγ(effort|yield) ∘ μ(resistance|edge) ∘ λ(attention|direction) + ε | :thermodynamic

δγ(effort|yield): The cycling of digestion; the work required to extract nutrition from the pattern.

μ(resistance|edge): The friction that generates heat; the resistance that makes the work meaningful.

λ(attention|direction): The directed energy of focus; the expenditure that shapes meaning.

ε: The uncertainty of return. High metabolic cost may yield nothing. That's the risk of lumemic patterns.

:state = thermodynamic

